text_blocks.content: 1 Instruction No. 13: Count Two: Enticement to Engage in an Illegal Sexual Activity - The Statute

The relevant statute for Count Two is Title 18, United States Code, Section 2422, which provides that "[w]hoever knowingly persuades, induces, entices, or coerces any individual to travel in interstate or foreign... commerce, or in any Territory or Possession of the United States, to engage in ... any sexual activity for which any person can be charged with a criminal offense," is guilty of a federal crime.
